				\begin{document}$$2{H}^{+}+2{e}^{-}\to {H}_{2}$$\end{document}, which consumes hydrogen ions; whereas, at high pH (pH = 10), the reaction at cathode consumes water rather than H+, being 2H2O+2e-→H2+2OH-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
